FBIS4-32958 "drlat105_a_94029" FBIS-LAT-94-105 Daily Report 27 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Film Institute, French Company Sign Distribution Contract Film Institute, French Company Sign Distribution Contract FL2805013994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 27 May 94 FL2805013994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] Sources at the (CAPA) French television production company have announced that they have signed a contract with Cuba granting them international rights to the purchase and distribution of Cuban Institute of Cinematographic Arts and Industry [ICAIC] films on video, which have never been seen outside of Cuba. These 35mm movies, most of which are in black and white, belong to the weekly magazines the ICAIC used to produce. AFP has confirmed that Cuban authorities will retain exclusive rights to the distribution of the documentaries in Latin America.
